# Server-spezifische Test-Patterns

> Detail-Referenz вЂ” geladen aus `TESTING.md` Index.

## Environment-Variable-Snapshot

Tests die `process.env` manipulieren, mГјssen den Originalzustand wiederherstellen:

```typescript
test("uses custom API key from env", async () => {
  const originalEnv = { ...process.env }
  try {
    process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY = "test-key-123"

    const result = await createClient()

    expect(result.apiKey).toBe("test-key-123")
  } finally {
    process.env = originalEnv
  }
}
```

### Alternativ mit `beforeEach`/`afterEach`

```typescript
describe("API Client", () => {
  const originalEnv = { ...process.env }

  afterEach(() => {
    process.env = { ...originalEnv }
  })

  test("falls back to default when key missing", async () => {
    delete process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY
    await expect(createClient()).rejects.toThrow(/API key/i)
  })
})
```

## Fetch-Mock mit Cleanup

```typescript
describe("AdjustmentAssistant", () => {
  const originalFetch = globalThis.fetch

  afterEach(() => {
    globalThis.fetch = originalFetch
  })

  test("sends structured request to provider", async () => {
    globalThis.fetch = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(
      new Response(JSON.stringify({ choices: [{ message: { content: "result" } }] })),
    )

    const result = await assistant.process("input")

    expect(result).toBe("result")
  })
})
```

## Async-Testing

Vitest unterstГјtzt async Tests nativ вЂ” kein spezielles Plugin nГ¶tig:

```typescript
// Async-Ergebnis prГјfen
test("compiles rules asynchronously", async () => {
  const rules = await compileRules(draftRules)
  expect(rules).toHaveLength(3)
})

// Async-Fehler prГјfen
test("rejects invalid rule format", async () => {
  await expect(compileRules(invalidInput)).rejects.toThrow(/invalid selector/i)
})
```

## Zod-Schema-Validierung testen

Teste Validierung mit echten Zod-Schemas, nicht Mocks:

```typescript
import { DraftRuleSchema } from "@chat-exporter/shared"

test("rejects rule without selector", () => {
  const result = DraftRuleSchema.safeParse({ effect: { type: "replace", value: "x" } })

  expect(result.success).toBe(false)
  expect(result.error?.issues[0].path).toContain("selector")
})

test.each(["heading", "paragraph", "code-block"])("accepts valid selector type: %s", (type) => {
  const result = DraftRuleSchema.safeParse({
    selector: { type, value: "test" },
    effect: { type: "replace", value: "changed" },
  })

  expect(result.success).toBe(true)
})
```

## Test-Imports

Server-Tests importieren Vitest-Globals explizit:

```typescript
import { describe, expect, test } from "vitest"
import type { AdjustmentSelection } from "@chat-exporter/shared"
```

## Testdatei-Platzierung

Tests liegen **neben dem Quellcode** (co-located):

```
apps/server/src/lib/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ adjustment-preview.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ adjustment-preview.test.ts
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ adjustment-assistant.ts
в””в”Ђв”Ђ adjustment-assistant.test.ts
```

# Mock-Standards

> Detail-Referenz вЂ” geladen aus `TESTING.md` Index.

## Nur an Integrationsgrenzen mocken

| Komponente | Warum mocken? | Wie mocken? |
|------------|---------------|-------------|
| `fetch` (externe APIs) | Externe Kosten, nicht-deterministisch | `globalThis.fetch = vi.fn()` |
| Environment-Variablen | KonfigurationsabhГ¤ngig | Snapshot/Restore-Pattern |
| Timer | Tests beschleunigen | `vi.useFakeTimers()` |

## Niemals mocken

| Komponente | Warum NICHT mocken? | Alternative |
|------------|---------------------|-------------|
| Zod-Validierung | Validierung ist Teil des Verhaltens | Teste echte Validierung |
| Shared-Package-Typen | Pure TypeScript, schnell, deterministisch | Nutze echte Typen |
| Interne Methoden | Implementierungsdetail | Teste nur Public API |
| Filesystem | Vitest bietet temporГ¤re Verzeichnisse | Nutze `vi.fn()` nur wenn wirklich nГ¶tig |

## Fetch-Mocking-Pattern

Das Projekt nutzt **direktes `globalThis.fetch`-Mocking** statt MSW:

```typescript
test("sends adjustment to API", async () => {
  // Arrange
  const mockFetch = vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(
    new Response(JSON.stringify({ reply: "Adjusted text" }), {
      status: 200,
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
    }),
  )
  globalThis.fetch = mockFetch

  // Act
  const result = await sendAdjustment("Make it shorter")

  // Assert
  expect(mockFetch).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()
  expect(result.reply).toBe("Adjusted text")
})
```

### Streaming-Response mocken

```typescript
function createMockStreamResponse(chunks: string[]): Response {
  const encoder = new TextEncoder()
  const stream = new ReadableStream({
    start(controller) {
      for (const chunk of chunks) {
        controller.enqueue(encoder.encode(`data: ${chunk}\n\n`))
      }
      controller.close()
    },
  })
  return new Response(stream, {
    headers: { "Content-Type": "text/event-stream" },
  })
}
```

## Mock-Interaktionen prГјfen

Nur observierbare Seiteneffekte prГјfen (Anzahl API-Calls, Parameter), **NICHT** exakte Prompt-Strings:

```typescript
// Gut: PrГјfe Anzahl der API-Calls
expect(mockFetch).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2)

// Gut: PrГјfe URL und Method
expect(mockFetch).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
  expect.stringContaining("/api/adjustments"),
  expect.objectContaining({ method: "POST" }),
)

// Schlecht: PrГјfe exakten Body-Text
expect(JSON.parse(mockFetch.mock.calls[0][1].body).prompt).toBe("Exact prompt text")
```

## `vi.fn()` vs `vi.spyOn()`

| Methode | Verwendung |
|---------|------------|
| `vi.fn()` | Komplett neue Mock-Funktion (z.B. `globalThis.fetch`) |
| `vi.spyOn(obj, "method")` | Bestehende Methode beobachten/Гјberschreiben, Original bleibt aufrufbar mit `.mockRestore()` |

```typescript
// vi.spyOn вЂ” beobachtet ohne zu ersetzen
const spy = vi.spyOn(console, "error").mockImplementation(() => {})
// ... Test ...
spy.mockRestore()
```

