## Task: Plan Step 0.2 вЂ” Create `parser-dom-kit.ts`

Extract shared DOM parsing helper functions used by both chatgpt-share-import.ts and generic-share-import.ts into a shared module.

### What to create

File: `apps/server/src/lib/parser-dom-kit.ts`

### Architecture Decision

The DOM helpers run inside `page.evaluate()` (browser context), NOT in Node. Both `chatgpt-share-import.ts` and `generic-share-import.ts` define the SAME helper functions inside their `page.evaluate()` callbacks. We need to extract these into a single shared source.

**Approach:** Export a `DOM_KIT_SCRIPT` string constant that, when injected into a browser page via `page.addInitScript({ content: DOM_KIT_SCRIPT })`, defines all shared helpers on `globalThis.__domKit`. The parsers then reference `__domKit.normalizeWhitespace()` etc. inside their `page.evaluate()` callbacks.

### Functions to extract

These functions are duplicated in both `chatgpt-share-import.ts` (lines 92-414) and `generic-share-import.ts` (inside page.evaluate). Extract all of them:

1. **Tag constants**: `wrapperTags`, `blockTags`, `codeLanguageLabels` (Set objects)
2. **`normalizeWhitespace(value)`** вЂ” Normalize Unicode spaces, collapse whitespace, trim
3. **`inlineText(node)`** вЂ” Recursively extract text from DOM nodes with Markdown formatting (bold, italic, code, links, strikethrough)
4. **`inlineFromElement(element)`** вЂ” Convenience wrapper: `normalizeWhitespace(Array.from(el.childNodes).map(inlineText).join(""))`
5. **`extractListItems(listElement, depth)`** вЂ” Recursively extract list items with indent depth
6. **`detectCodeLanguage(preElement)`** вЂ” Detect language from first line or CSS class hints
7. **`extractCodeText(preElement)`** вЂ” Extract code content, strip language label / copy button text
8. **`extractTable(tableElement)`** вЂ” Extract headers and rows from table element
9. **`elementToBlocks(element)`** вЂ” Convert any element to an array of block objects (paragraph, heading, list, code, quote, table)

### Implementation

```typescript
// parser-dom-kit.ts

/**
 * Browser-injectable script that defines shared DOM parsing helpers on globalThis.__domKit.
 * 
 * Usage in parser files:
 *   await page.addInitScript({ content: DOM_KIT_SCRIPT });
 *   const result = await page.evaluate(() => {
 *     const { normalizeWhitespace, elementToBlocks } = globalThis.__domKit;
 *     // ... use helpers ...
 *   });
 */
export const DOM_KIT_SCRIPT: string = `(function() {
  const wrapperTags = new Set(["ARTICLE", "SECTION", "DIV", "SPAN", "FIGURE", "MAIN"]);
  const blockTags = new Set(["P", "H1", "H2", "H3", "H4", "H5", "H6", "UL", "OL", "PRE", "BLOCKQUOTE", "TABLE", "HR"]);
  const codeLanguageLabels = new Set(["plain text", "text", "json", "javascript", "typescript", "ts", "js", "python", "bash", "shell", "sql", "html", "css", "markdown", "md", "yaml", "yml"]);

  function normalizeWhitespace(value) {
    return (value ?? "")
      .replace(/\\u00a0/g, " ")
      .replace(/\\r/g, "")
      .replace(/[ \\t\\f\\v]+/g, " ")
      .replace(/ *\\n */g, "\\n")
      .replace(/\\n{3,}/g, "\\n\\n")
      .trim();
  }

  // ... (copy all other functions from chatgpt-share-import.ts lines 147-414) ...
  // These functions are identical in both files.

  globalThis.__domKit = {
    wrapperTags, blockTags, codeLanguageLabels,
    normalizeWhitespace, inlineText, inlineFromElement,
    extractListItems, detectCodeLanguage, extractCodeText,
    extractTable, elementToBlocks,
  };
})();`;

/** TypeScript interface describing what __domKit provides in browser context. */
export interface DomKit {
  wrapperTags: Set&lt;string&gt;;
  blockTags: Set&lt;string&gt;;
  codeLanguageLabels: Set&lt;string&gt;;
  normalizeWhitespace: (value: string | null | undefined) => string;
  inlineText: (node: Node) => string;
  inlineFromElement: (element: Element) => string;
  extractListItems: (listElement: Element, depth?: number) => string[];
  detectCodeLanguage: (preElement: HTMLElement) => string;
  extractCodeText: (preElement: HTMLElement) => string;
  extractTable: (tableElement: HTMLTableElement) => { type: "table"; headers: string[]; rows: string[][] } | null;
  elementToBlocks: (element: Element) => Array&lt;Record&lt;string, unknown&gt;&gt;;
}

// Augment globalThis for browser context
declare global {
  var __domKit: DomKit;
}
```

### Source Code Reference

Read the functions from `apps/server/src/lib/chatgpt-share-import.ts` lines 92-414 (inside the `page.evaluate()` callback). Copy them EXACTLY (they work in browser context, using raw JS/TS DOM APIs). Ensure the string version has correct escaping (especially regex patterns with backslashes).

IMPORTANT: In the string, you must double-escape backslashes used in regex. For example, `\u00a0` in TypeScript becomes `\\u00a0` in the string. `\r` becomes `\\r`, `\n` becomes `\\n`, `\t` becomes `\\t`, etc. Same for regex character classes.

Also read `apps/server/src/lib/generic-share-import.ts` to confirm the functions are identical. The generic version's `normalizeWhitespace` accepts `string | null | undefined` (with `(value ?? "")`), while the ChatGPT version accepts `string`. Use the more permissive signature.

